The course introduces the learning professional approach and the teacher's professional agency model that are applied in the analysis of the student's life and learning experience to the creation of a teaching vision at the level of the individual and the group of teachers. Cultural, structural and material factors affecting the teacher's work, including regulations affecting the teacher's work, are introduced. Evidence-based methods are introduced to enhance collaboration with different parties. The possibilities of inquiry-based approach to support the professional development of teachers is analysed. The process of compiling educational regulations is discussed and the possibilities of contributing to it will be examined.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To support the development of the teacher's personal and collective agency and taking active role both in the teachers' community and in society.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has passed the subject: 1) Understands how the teacher's agency and professionalism is formed. 2) Evaluates how his / her own biography, practical knowledge and values and attitudes allow him / her to work as a teacher. 3) Creates a vision of his / her teaching that integrates personal and professional long-term goals. 4) Understands how cultural, structural and material factors at different levels affect the work of a teacher. 5) Is able to apply evidence-based methods of teacher collaboration and inquiry-based approach to form teachers' shared professional knowledge and vision. 6) Is able to apply evidence-based methods for collaboration with learners' families and local community. 7) Understands how educational regulations are developed and how to contribute to it, e.g. through professional associations and expert groups in the field.
